Cap. CXCVIII. <foreign xml:lang="grc">Ἀρίσαρον</foreign> natum esse ex <foreign xml:lang="grc">ἄρις</foreign> ἢ <foreign xml:lang="grc">ἴσα-<lb break="no"/>ρον</foreign>, <hi rend="italic">aris</hi>, <hi rend="italic">quae similis aro</hi>, auguratur Salmasius.<ref target="#fn6">⁶</ref> Nam-<lb break="no"/>que Plinius scribit: „Est et <hi rend="italic">aris</hi>, quae in Aegypto na-<lb break="no"/>scitur, minor tamen minoribusque foliis, et utique radi-<lb break="no"/>ce, quae tamen olivae grandis magnitudinem implet.“<ref target="#fn7">⁷</ref><lb/>
Sic et <foreign xml:lang="grc">ἄρις</foreign> Galeno<ref target="#fn8">⁸</ref> ac Hesychio plantae genus est.<lb/>
Duo autem Arisara italica Anguillara proponit<ref target="#fn9">⁹</ref>: al-<lb break="no"/>terum foliis angustis lanceolatis, haud procul a Roma,<lb/>
